<paragraph blockId="46.[144,1101,206,325]" pageId="46" pageNumber="730">
Widespread across the Palaearctic Region, missing only in the Russian Far East and the Iberian Peninsula; introduced also to North America (
<bibRefCitation author="Hansen M" box="[866,1018,238,262]" pageId="46" pageNumber="730" refId="ref16901" refString="Hansen M. 1999. World catalogue of insects. Volume 2. Hydrophiloidea (s. str.) (Coleoptera). Stenstrup: Apollo Books." type="book" year="1999">Hansen 1999</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hansen M" box="[1031,1089,238,262]" pageId="46" pageNumber="730" pagination="36 - 68" refId="ref16930" refString="Hansen M. 2004. Hydrophiloidea. pp. 36 - 68. In: Lobl I, Smetana A. editors. Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera, Vol. 2. Stenstrup: Apollo Books; 942 pp." type="book chapter" year="2004">2004</bibRefCitation>
). The species was recorded from İçel by 
<bibRefCitation author="Peyron E" box="[602,766,270,294]" pageId="46" pageNumber="730" pagination="353 - 434" refId="ref18430" refString="Peyron E. 1858. Catalogue des coleopteres des environs de Tarsous (Caramanie). Ann Soc Entomol Fr. (3) 6: 353 - 434." type="journal article" year="1858">Peyron (1858)</bibRefCitation>
, but his record is in need of confirmation.
</paragraph>
